subject: p16553329

There is mild pulmonary vascular engorgement and small bilateral pleural effusions which have decreased in size compared to the previous exam. Patchy bibasilar airspace opacities likely reflect atelectasis, but infection is not fully excluded. No pneumothorax is demonstrated. Multilevel degenerative changes are noted in the thoracic spine.
Impression: Small bilateral pleural effusions, mild pulmonary vascular engorgement, and bibasilar atelectasis. Infection, however, within the lung bases cannot be completely excluded.
